  "prompt": "Why India's performance is still poor in olympics?",
  "response": "India's poor performance in the Olympics can be attributed to several factors:\n\n1. Limited Sports Infrastructure\n- Lack of world-class training facilities\n- Inadequate sports infrastructure in most states\n- Limited investment in sports development\n\n2. Financial Constraints\n- Insufficient government funding for athletes\n- Limited sponsorship opportunities\n- Low financial support for training and international exposure\n\n3. Cultural Factors\n- Emphasis on academic education over sports\n- Limited societal encouragement for sports careers\n- Preference for traditional sports like cricket\n\n4. Talent Identification and Development\n- Weak grassroots sports programs\n- Limited talent scouting mechanisms\n- Lack of systematic athlete development system\n\n5. Coaching Quality\n- Shortage of professional and experienced coaches\n- Outdated training methodologies\n- Limited international exposure for coaches\n\n6. Limited Participation\n- Low participation in multiple Olympic sports\n- Concentration in few sports like wrestling, boxing, badminton\n- Weak performance in team sports\n\n7. Economic Challenges\n- Limited resources for athletes from economically weaker backgrounds\n- High cost of international training and competitions\n\n8. Systemic Issues\n- Bureaucratic sports administration\n- Lack of transparency in selection processes\n- Ineffective sports governance\n\nRecent improvements in government initiatives and private investments are gradually addressing these challenges.",
